Join us in Todos Santos!

Please join us for our computational biology workshop at the CSU Center in Todos Santos, Mexico. Here is a summary of the topics that we are looking forward to covering over the course of the week.



Computational Workshop

Instructors: Kim Hoke, Tai Montgomery, Dan Sloan, Mark Stenglein

Monday May 9: Introduction to high-throughput sequencing, computational biology, and code management

  • 09:00-09:30 Arrival and Check-In
  • 09:30-10:30 Introduction to Todos Santos and Group Discussion [slides]
  • 10:30-12:00 High-Throughput Sequencing Technologies [slides]
  • 12:00-13:00 Lunch
  • 13:00-14:30 UNIX and Command Line Tools (part I) [slides]
  • 14:30-16:00 UNIX and Command Line Tools (part II) [UNIX commands sheet]
  • 16:00-17:00 Workflow Manangement (Snakemake) [slides]

Tuesday May 10: RNA-seq

  • 08:00-08:45 Breakfast
  • 09:00-12:00 RNA-seq Data Analysis I [slides]
  • 12:00-13:00 Lunch
  • 13:00-17:00 RNA-seq Data Analysis II

Wednesday May 11: Genomic analysis tools

  • 08:00-08:45 Breakfast
  • 09:00-10:00 Introduction to Genomic Analysis [slides]
  • 10:00-12:00 Manipulating and Obtaining Genomics Data [slides]
  • 12:00-13:00 Lunch
  • 13:00-14:30 Alignment and Read Mapping [slides]
  • 14:30-16:00 Assembly and Annotation [slides]
  • 16:00-17:00 Variant Calling
  • 18:00-20:00 Workshop Dinner

Thursday May 12: Data Visualization

  • 08:00-08:45 Breakfast
  • 09:00-10:00 Code Management (GitHub)
  • 10:00-10:30 Introduction to R, R Markdown, and Data Visualization [slides]
  • 10:30-12:00 Plotting Genomic Data with R and ggplot
  • 12:00-13:00 Lunch
  • 13:00-14:00 Figure Drawing in R
  • 14:00-15:00 Circular Representations of Genomic Data with Circos
  • 15:00-16:00 Local BLAST and Comparative Genomics [slides]
  • 16:00 End of workshop
